      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOUTHAMPTON FLARE (2) looks a top chance. Bombed the start at first run for the new yard so forgive that one but has since won maiden here two back then was runner-up behind Ankle Rolex latest. Many horses in this come through that race and Ankle Rolex is in the first today. Winning rider stays aboard this one and is drawn to stalk the leaders. Go close. RISING WATER (7) has placed five on end including a third behind SOUTHAMPTON FLARE latest. Meets him marginally better and long overdue for a win. Low draw and gets chance. NO I'M NOT (6) was well below expectations latest but the start prior stormed home to score. Aided by the regular claimer and will be tough to stop. Stablemate JULY (4) was sixth behind Ankle Rolex last time and is another who gets home hard. GALAXY GENERAL (1) was fourth in the Ankle Rolex race and has claims off the inside draw.",
